The paper deals with the problem of storing dynamic data in distributed storage systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also considers the use of side information to improve the storage cost, which is a topic that falls under the categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
